<heading id="F84281FBC23F6F2EFF4D89DAFDE65EBD" box="[166,629,655,682]" fontSize="36" level="2" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" reason="3">
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFF4D89DAFDE65EBD" authority="Kandybina, 1972" authorityName="Kandybina" authorityYear="1972" box="[166,629,655,682]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFF4D89DAFE3B5EBE" bold="true" box="[166,424,655,682]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Rhagoletis mongolica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFE4489DAFDE65EBD" author="Kandybina, M. N." box="[431,629,655,681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="540 - 545" refId="ref13266" refString="Kandybina, M. N. 1972. Fruit flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the Mongolian People's Republic. Entomological Review, 51, 540 - 545." type="journal article" year="1972">Kandybina, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A30A3697C23F6F2EFF4D89E8FBDC5EFA" blockId="14.[166,1225,701,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFF4D89E8FEEF5EC7" author="Kandybina, M. N." box="[166,380,701,723]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="540 - 545" refId="ref13266" refString="Kandybina, M. N. 1972. Fruit flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the Mongolian People's Republic. Entomological Review, 51, 540 - 545." type="journal article" year="1972">Kandybina, 1972: 913</bibRefCitation>
(description), 1977 (larva; distribution; host plants; new records); 
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFBF989E8FF655EFA" author="Korneyev, V. A. &amp; Merz, B." pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="55 - 64" refId="ref13531" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Merz, B. 1997. A new species of Rhagoletis Loew (Diptera: Tephritidae), with notes on Central Asian species. Journal of Ukrainian Entomological Society, 3 (1), 55 - 64." type="journal article" year="1997">Korneyev &amp; Merz, 1997: 63</bibRefCitation>
(key); 
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFED3898DFDBD5EFA" author="Norrbom, A. L. &amp; Carroll, L. E. &amp; Thompson, F. C. &amp; White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[312,558,728,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="65 - 251" refId="ref14248" refString="Norrbom, A. L., Carroll, L. E., Thompson, F. C., White, I. M., Freidberg, A. 1999. Systematic database of names. In: Thompson, F. C., ed. Fruit Fly Expert Identification System and Systematic Information Database. Myia (1998), 9, 65 - 251 &amp; Diptera Data Dissemination Disk (CD - ROM) (1998) 1." type="journal article" year="1999">Norrbom et al., 1999: 201</bibRefCitation>
(catalogue); 
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFD42898DFB815EFA" author="Korneyev, V. A. &amp; Ovchinnikova, O. G." box="[681,1042,728,750]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="456 - 564" refId="ref13578" refString="Korneyev, V. A., Ovchinnikova, O. G. 2004. 79. Tephritidae - pestrokrylki [fruit flies]. In: Lehr, P. A, ed. Key to the insects of Russian Far East. Vol. VI. Diptera and Siphonaptera. Pt. 3. 659 pp. Dal'nauka, Vladivostok, pp. 456 - 564 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="2004">Korneyev &amp; Ovchinnikova, 2004: 482</bibRefCitation>
(key).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBAF651CC23F6F2EFF308850FC01580B" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A30A3697C23F6F2EFF308850FC01580B" blockId="14.[166,1225,772,1055]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Comments. This species was originally described based on a single female and a third instar larva reared from 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFDFB8870FD465F2A" box="[528,725,804,830]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cupressaceae" genus="Juniperus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sabina">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFDFB8870FD465F2A" box="[528,725,804,830]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Juniperus sabina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
L. in 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFCF68871FC1C5F2A" box="[797,911,804,830]" name="Mongolia" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Mongolia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFC4B8871FBE35F2B" author="Kandybina, M. N." box="[928,1136,804,831]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="540 - 545" refId="ref13266" refString="Kandybina, M. N. 1972. Fruit flies (Diptera, Tephritidae) of the Mongolian People's Republic. Entomological Review, 51, 540 - 545." type="journal article" year="1972">Kandybina, 1972</bibRefCitation>
). Later, the larva was redescribed based on material from the same host plant in 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFBAF8810FB5B5F4B" box="[1092,1224,837,863]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="C7244B66C23F6F2EFF458831FEEF5F6B" author="Kandybina, M. N." box="[174,380,868,895]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="1 - 212" refId="ref13296" refString="Kandybina, M. N. 1977. The larvae of fruit-flies (Diptera: Tephritidae). Nauka, Leningrad, 1 - 212 [In Russian]." type="book chapter" year="1977">Kandybina, 1977</bibRefCitation>
). The adult specimens from 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFD2C8830FCD85F6B" box="[711,843,869,895]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
were briefly described as having completely black femora and partly black tibiae; neither their male nor female genitalia have been described. We therefore consider 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFD4788F0FCD15FAA" authorityName="Kandybina" authorityYear="1972" box="[684,834,932,959]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFD4788F0FD2D5FAA" box="[684,702,933,958]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFD2088F1FCD15FAA" box="[715,834,932,958]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to have entirely yellow femora as in the 
<typeStatus id="7C0E8835C23F6F2EFF1B8891FEC95FCA" box="[240,346,964,990]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">holotype</typeStatus>
, and the Kyrgyz specimens to be likely non-conspecific. The geographically “intermediate form” from 
<collectingCountry id="DBA27607C23F6F2EFE0F88B0FDFB5FEB" box="[484,616,997,1023]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
must be analyzed to clarify its taxonomic position and molecular differences from both 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFDB18F50FD63580A" authorityName="Kandybina" authorityYear="1972" box="[602,752,1028,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mongolica">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFDB18F50FDFF580A" box="[602,620,1029,1054]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFD928F51FD63580A" box="[633,752,1028,1054]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">mongolica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="64B54D14C23F6F2EFCC18F50FC18580A" authorityName="Korneyev &amp; Smith &amp; Hulbert &amp; Frey &amp; Korneyev" authorityYear="2022" box="[810,907,1029,1055]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Rhagoletis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="merzi">
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFCC18F50FCAF580A" box="[810,828,1029,1054]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">R</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="91C1EA85C23F6F2EFCA28F50FC18580A" box="[841,907,1029,1054]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">merzi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
